An overview of modern molecular immunology.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is acquiring knowledge in the basics of immunology, developing understanding of the basic principles of contemporary molecular immunology and immunogenetics, gaining the ability to use this knowledge in practice and understanding the development and evolution of the immune system.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student has acquired the basics of immunology, understands them, and is able to describe the response of the innate and adaptive immune system to various antigens. The student knows the organs, cells and molecules of the immune system and special features of the immunogenetics. The student knows some diseases caused by deviations in the functioning of the immune system. Knows the main methods applied in laboratory work both for studying immunology and related those applying immunological principles. Knows the main model organisms used for studying immunology. The student understands the development and relationship of different parts of immune system from evolutionary perspective.
